{
  "stem": "4361.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the why was understood about a week later when the next orders came.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You have 12 hours to pack, and we'll put you-- and the Jews will be put in a ghetto.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then it became clear that the reason these 21-- I believe there were 21-- Jewish known members of the Jewish community where imprisoned was that they be kept as hostages in case something happens in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You see, we did not know about the Warsaw Ghetto Uprising, which happened just about a year before.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But the Nazis knew, and this time they wanted to make sure that if anything happens, they have hostages.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And nothing is going to happen while they deport the Sighet Jews to the ghetto. 12 hours later, early in the morning-- it was the week after Passover, so it must have been end of April, early May.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "End of April, I believe.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And Sighet is a very beautiful town, and it was the time when the lilacs began to bloom.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The lilac in my mother's garden was very special, because it was double petaled purple lilac.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And you could see already the buds.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And this was the morning when they rang, and again, the gendarmes-- and we were packed by then, mother and I and the cook.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And across the street, my brother's wife, Rose, Roshe, Rose, and the two little babies, my nieces-- we had our valises.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And in the street where we lived, there were few Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "It was a mixed neighborhood, so there were about four Jewish families.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And they were all packed, and the gendarmes came, and they took us into towards another street where there were some more Jews.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
